commit.message: Cancel macos build on docker build fail

Add AppImage build (#259)

* Add appimage support

WIP: This is probably only compatible when used with
CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX.

* Support data-less appimages

Ini file can now be configured to set the datapath relative to the
appimage path. Useful for dev bins where the tester already has their
own copy of data.

* Update snapshot to build appimage

Also add easy-to-use build-appimage.sh script.

* Add 7z to appimage

* Add docker snapshot support

* Fix build-appimage for older cmake

Required for dockerimage of bionic. Also add wget to bionic image

* AppImage: build mapeditor

* Improve appimage build environment

* AppImage script builds all programs

* fix for gh actions

* Add gtk plugins so mapeditor and g3dviewer work

* Fix g3dviewer and editor so they work as AppImages

* Fix code + cmake.
* Add instructions for installing snapshot.

* (Re-)Run cmake (and thus snapshot) build if docker image updated

* Better job name

* Add Prerelease workflow

* Attempts to get prerelease working

* next attempt

* Allow re-release

* Don't update body if one already exists

Allows making a custom body without it getting overwritten

* remove snapshot instructions (we'll add these elsewhere later)

* Test with commit id

* Don't update name in prerelease

* Complete CI setup

* Update .github/workflows/docker.yml

Co-authored-by: Andy Alt <andy5995@users.noreply.github.com>
